          "subtype": "ability",
          "text": "Killia's individuality still rests within the cocoon, yet trying to resist assimilation. If a PC succeeds at a DC 32 Diplomacy check on the cocoon, the cocoon takes 5d6 mental damage and is stunned 1 as Killia's consciousness fights the Weaver. The cocoon can't be affected in this way more than once per turn.",
          "type": "stat_block_section"
        },
        {
          "ability_type": "automatic",
          "action_type": {
            "name": "Free Action",
            "subtype": "action_type",
            "type": "stat_block_section"
          },
          "name": "Give of Oneself",
          "subtype": "ability",
          "trigger": "The Weaver would be reduced to 0 Hit Points; Effect The cocoon's vitality is linked to the Weaver's. It loses 30 Hit Points, restoring 15 Hit Points to the Weaver. It can use this ability even if it would otherwise be unable to act.",
          "type": "stat_block_section"
        }
      ],
